definitions.definition: To be made up of; to consist of (especially a comprehensive list of parts).
examples: The parts are comprised by the whole.
Our committee comprises a president, secretary, treasurer and five other members.
The whole is comprised of the parts.
definitions.label_groups: sometimes proscribed , usually in the passive

definitions.definition: To include, contain, or be made up of, defining the minimum elements, whether essential or inessential to define an invention.

main_definition: ( transitive ) To be made up of; to consist of (especially a comprehensive list of parts). [from the earlier 15th c.]
secondary_definitions: ( sometimes proscribed , usually in the passive ) To compose ; to constitute . [from the 17th c.]
( patent law ) To include, contain, or be made up of, defining the minimum elements, whether essential or inessential to define an invention.
